---
import DefaultLayout from '@layouts/DefaultLayout.astro'
import PageHeader from '@components/PageHeader.astro'
import { Card } from 'accessible-astro-components'
import { Heading } from 'accessible-astro-components'
import { Link } from 'accessible-astro-components'
---
<DefaultLayout title="Teaching">
    <PageHeader
        title="Teaching"
        subtitle="I've been teaching and presenting on design for years, mostly in virtual small group settings."
        bgType="bordered"
        showBreadcrumbs=""
    />

    <section class="my-12">
        <div class="container space-content">
            <div class="my-3 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
                <Card
                img="/presentations/object-mapping.png"
                url=""
                title="Object Mapping: The Backbone of OOUX"
                footer="Dec 11, 2025"
                >
                    We learned how to discover and model objects along with their attributes.
                </Card>
                <Card
                img="/presentations/improve-signup.png"
                url=""
                title="Improving the signup experience"
                footer="Oct 1, 2025"
                >
                    I led an in-person workshop to explore "hot spots" that were causing friction in our signup experience, and come up with ways to improve it.
                </Card>
                <Card
                img="/presentations/ooux-style-sketching.png"
                url=""
                title="OOUX-Style Sketching & Wireframing"
                footer="Sep 11, 2025"
                >
                    I demonstrated how OOUX helps us translate conceptual models directly into the UI.
                </Card>
                <Card
                img="/presentations/intro-to-ooux.png"
                url=""
                title="An Introduction to Object-Oriented UX (OOUX)"
                footer="Aug 21, 2025"
                >
                    OOUX is a powerful philosophy for digital product design. It has become the foundation of my design practice, and calls for a lot of collaboration. So I invited as many people from UX, Product, Engineering, and Marketing as I could. We had a good turnout!
                </Card>
                <Card
                img="/presentations/figma-make.png"
                url=""
                title="Figma Make: What I've Learned from Years of Prototyping & How Figma Make Can Help"
                footer="Aug 7, 2025"
                >
                    I've prototyped using tools like Balsamiq, pen and paper, spreadsheets, Sketch, Figma, and HTML+CSS. Emerging AI prototyping tools like Figma Make are extremely useful, but require careful handling.
                </Card>
                <Card
                img="/presentations/problem-definition.png"
                url=""
                title="Sharpening the Axe: A Case for Problem Definition"
                footer="Feb 13, 2025"
                >
                    I led a discussion on why and how to define problems before attempting to solve them, drawing heavily from Bill Burnett and Dave Evans' book <em>Designing You (New) Work Life</em>. We then did a problem reframing exercise using a real situation described in a post on Reddit (r/careerguidance).
                </Card>
